gomodel:SYNGO_1837  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: TARP γ-4 is an integral membrane protein found in the postsynaptic density membrane.\n\nFig. 6A: \"TARPs colocalize with AMPARs at excitatory synapses.\" Subcellular fractionation and western blot analysis showed TARP γ-4 is enriched in synaptosomes and is resistant to extraction from synaptic membranes with Triton X-100 (PSDI-II fractions), indicating a strong association with the PSD.\n'integral component of postsynaptic density membrane (GO:0099061)' is based on (1) the transmembrane topology of the TARP γ-4 and (2) the known interaction with AMPARs (plasma membrane proteins) at the PSD (3) TARP γ-4 regulation the decay of synaptic AMPAR currents in cerebellar granule cells (see BP annotation)... Experimental description: From text: \"To determine the cellular distribution of the TARPs, we performed in situ hybridization on sagittal and coronal sections of adult rat brain with 35S-labeled antisense probes, which revealed..\"\n\"...We also explored the developmental course of TARP expression during rat ontogeny. Western blotting of brain cerebral cortex homogenates shows that..\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
